# Secure Azure VM Infrastructure Lab Series

-Built a secure VM infrastructure in Microsoft Azure with no public IP exposure, using NSG firewall simulation and Azure Bastion for RDP. Add commentMore actions
-Demonstrated cloud networking, access control, and secure remote access configuration.

---

## 🔧 What I Did

- Created a Resource Group, Virtual Network (VNet), and subnet
- Configured Network Security Groups (NSG) to simulate a firewall
- Deployed a Windows Server VM with no public IP
- Connected securely using Azure Bastion
- Documented steps and added screenshots

---

## 🛠️ Tools Used

- Microsoft Azure Portal
- Windows Server 2019 Datacenter
- Azure Bastion
- Git & GitHub for version control

---

## 📸 Screenshots Captured

- Resource Group
- VNet & Subnet with IP range
- NSG rules
- VM Networking (no public IP)
- Azure Bastion browser-based RDP session

> You’ll find these screenshots inside the `/screenshots` folder.

